text:
 Divide the Skittles into colors. Separate them into different bowls, for example, reds goes in one, oranges goes in another, etc. Powder each color. Use a food processor to thoroughly powder each color. Discard any chunks left over. Ensure that the food processor is thoroughly cleaned out before powdering a different color. Coat the marshmallows. Use the water as an adhesive. Finger dipping: Dip a marshmallow in the water. Gently shake any excess water off before rolling it into a Skittle bowl. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/a\/a2\/Make-Skittles-Marshmallow-Pops-Step-3Bullet1-Version-2.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-Skittles-Marshmallow-Pops-Step-3Bullet1-Version-2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/a\/a2\/Make-Skittles-Marshmallow-Pops-Step-3Bullet1-Version-2.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-Skittles-Marshmallow-Pops-Step-3Bullet1-Version-2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

